lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

dc:date  a      owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4535  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Traf6 is the E3 ubiquitin ligase that mediates constitutive K63 ubiquitination of PSD-95 (DLG4) (SynGO annotation #4898). Together with its deubiquitinase counterpart CYLD it controls PSD-95's clustering efficacy in spines and in turn controls cell surface availability of NMDA receptors in the postsynaptic membrane.\n\n\"CYLD mediates NMDA-induced rapid PSD-95 declustering from spines\" by deubiquitination of K63 (Fig. 8) upon CYLD knock down via shRNA (Panel E,F).\n\n\"... K63-polyUb plays an essential role in synaptic maintenance and orderly organization of PSD-95 and LTD. PSD-95 is constitutively conjugated by K63-polyUb chains (by Ubc13/Uev1A-TRAF6), which maintains and compartmentalizes the protein (perhaps combined with other posttranslational modifications) to specific subdomains within the PSD. Synaptic activity opens NMDARs, allowing Ca2+ influx, and recruits/activates CYLD ..., which subsequently removes K63-polyUb from PSD-95.\" (Fig. 9)\n\nSilencing CYLD in hippocampal neurons abolishes NMDA-induced chemical long-term depression (Fig. 9).. Experimental description: \"CYLD is required for cLTD. (A) NMDA (50 μM, 9 min)-triggered sGluA1 internalization in cultured rat hippocampal neurons infected with indicated plasmids.\" Figure legend Fig. 9." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2023-01-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4535" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

